Senator Benjamin Uwajumogu, representing Imo North district in the Nigerian Senate is dead. Uwajumogu died on Wednesday. He was a member of the All Progressives Congress (APC). Uwajumogu was born June 30, 1968 in Okigwe, Ihitte Uboma in Imo. He was a former speaker of the Imo State House of Assembly and was elected into the 9th Senate after a supplementary election. On July 25, the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) issued a Certificate of Return to Uwajumogu after an order of Justice Taiwo Taiwo of a Federal High Court, Abuja. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.